   decreased performance IQ in boys, but PFOS {[}beta = 1.56, 95\% CI =
   0.06, 3.06; exposure = per 1 ln (ng/ml) increase] increased performance
   IQ in girls. PFAS are associated with executive function impairments in
   children, but not related to behavioral difficulty in children.},
