   metamorphopsia after rhegmatogenous retinal detachment surgery was
   performed using Review Manager 5.4 statistical software.ResultsA total
   of 12 studies reported 1133 participants with 469 patients with
   postoperative metamorphopsia. The meta-analysis showed a higher
   incidence of metamorphopsia in macular-off cases compared with
   macular-on RRD (RR = 2.88, 95\% CI: 2.35 to 3.52). The use of
   perfluorocarbon liquid (PFCL) during pars plana vitrectomy (PPV) reduced
   the incidence of metamorphopsia (RR = 0.61, 95\% CI: 0.41 to 0.92).
   There was no evidence of any important difference in metamorphopsia
