   was associated with greatest risk (adjusted odds ratio, 4.21; 95\%
   confidence interval, 2.00-8.88). There was minimal evidence of
   interaction by child sex or occupational pesticide exposure, and no
   monotonic dose-response pattern with frequency of use (times per
